title: Refactored server preferences.
message:
Refactored server preferences.
Previously, the hostName was stored in the preferences. Now the code (ex : US) is stored and the hostName is matched in the PADServer enum.
This allows to update the hostname easily (no need to force the user to re-check the updated server or to write custom code to update the preferences)

message: Fixed #34 : when a monster is both "normal" monster (exp, skill-ups, awakenings ...) and a material, all new monsters were treated as materials and it was not possible to create a new monster. Fixed by keeping the monster both as a material update and a new monsters. That duplicates the monster until the next sync, but it's the best I could come up with.
